Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.00,0:00:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose it all started with the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.12,0:00:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it's a very special kind of snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.55,0:00:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A snow to make the happy happier and the giddy even giddier.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.69,0:00:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A snow to make a homecoming homier
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.68,0:00:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and natural enemies friends, naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.02,0:00:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For it was the first snow of the season.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.64,0:00:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And as any child can tell you, there's a certain magic to the very first snow...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.66,0:00:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when it falls on the day before Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.61,0:00:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,For when the first snow is also a Christmas snow... [Laughing]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.39,0:01:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, something wonderful is bound to happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.10,0:01:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[Children laughing]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.88,0:01:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[Ruler tapping] Children, back to your seats.  The snow can wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.58,0:01:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now.  I've hired professor Hinkle, the magician,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.10,0:01:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to entertain at today's class Christmas party, so pay attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.47,0:01:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Professor Hinkle was just about the worst magician in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.80,0:01:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,[BONK, PING, TINKLE, SCRABBLE, DOINK]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.86,0:01:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I put the magic eggs in to my hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.59,0:01:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Abracadabra, to coin a phrase... [Laugh]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.15,0:01:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And voila the eggs have turned in to...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.10,0:01:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Messy messy messy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.37,0:02:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[Children groan]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.85,0:02:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Where IS that rabbit?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.62,0:02:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hocus Pocus! Where ARE you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.10,0:02:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Bah, the only thing this hat's good for is the trash can!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.30,0:02:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,[Children laugh]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.66,0:02:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,[Bell rings][Children cheer]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.94,0:02:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[Hinkle grumbles]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.70,0:02:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look at the snow!  It's cold and snowy! It's the best kind of snow!  [etc.]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.12,0:02:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're building a snowman, Karen. You make the head!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.50,0:03:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The head is the most difficult part, ask anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.86,0:03:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What will we call him?  Should we call him Harold?  Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.48,0:03:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[Mumbling]? Oh, No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.84,0:03:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oatmeal? Oatmeal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.48,0:03:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How about... Frosty?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.66,0:03:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Frosty?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.26,0:03:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Frosty it is.  Frosty the snowman!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.90,0:03:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[Cheers]
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.38,0:03:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[Frosty the snowman, what a happy, jolly soul. With a corn-cob pipe and a button nose, and two eyes made out of coal.]
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.71,0:03:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Frosty the snow - 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.09,0:03:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come back here, YOU!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.20,0:03:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,HAPPY BIRTHDAY!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.10,0:04:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That hat brought Frosty to life.  It must be magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.36,0:04:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Magic?  My hat, magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.72,0:04:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.52,0:04:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If that hat is magic, I want it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.42,0:04:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not yours anymore! You threw it away!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.62,0:04:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't talk back to your elders, you naughty naughty little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.58,0:04:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, stay in there, or there will be no carrots for Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.64,0:04:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't take that hat back, it brought Frosty to life
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.92,0:04:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw it happen! I saw nothing of the kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.62,0:04:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw nothing of the kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.16,0:04:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[Chattering]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.44,0:04:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet, I can't lose that hat if it's really got magic now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.78,0:04:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll make me a billionaire magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.08,0:04:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But we saw Frosty come to life, didn't we? Uh-huh, we sure did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.32,0:04:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You silly children believe everything you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.32,0:05:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're grown up you'll realize that snowmen can't come to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.96,0:05:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But we -
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.26,0:05:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Silly, silly silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.56,0:05:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, Frosty, we don't care what grown-ups say, we know you DID come to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.68,0:05:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We know, Frosty.  We just know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.80,0:05:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[Frosty the snowman, was a jolly, happy soul. With a corn-cob pipe and a button nose, and two eyes made out of coal.]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.82,0:05:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,[Frosty the snowman is a fairy-tale they say. He was made of snow but the children know how he came to life one day.]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.76,0:05:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, the hat DID belong to Frosty and the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.76,0:05:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That part must be made very clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.20,0:06:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, Hocus Pocus was entirely in the right in what he was about to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.96,0:06:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Hocus Pocus raced back to the children just as fast as he could.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.12,0:06:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[Hocus Pocus whistles]
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.86,0:06:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!  The hat's back.  Let's see if it will make Frosty alive again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.18,0:06:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,HAPPY BIRTHDAY!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.10,0:06:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I said my first words... but snowmen can't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.84,0:06:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, come on now, what's the joke. Could I really be alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.04,0:07:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I can make words, I can move. I can juggle, I can sweep, I can count to 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.92,0:07:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 9, 6, 8... Well, I can count to 5. [laughing]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.02,0:07:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you know?  I'm even ticklish.  In fact, I'm all living.  I AM alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.16,0:07:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What a neat thing to happen to a nice guy like me.  [Children cheer]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.92,0:07:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,[There must have been some magic in that old silk hat they found.]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.40,0:07:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,[For when they placed it on his head he began to dance around.]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.08,0:07:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[Frosty the snowman was alive as he could be and the children say he could laugh and play just the same as you and me.]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.46,0:08:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.40,0:08:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Frosty?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.58,0:08:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew, is there a thermometer around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.58,0:08:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there on the wall, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.66,0:08:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I was afraid of that.  The thermomter is getting red.  I hate red thermometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.06,0:08:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, Frosty?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.66,0:08:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,'Cause when the thermometer gets all reddish, the temperature goes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.30,0:08:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the temperature goes up, I start to melt.  And when I start to melt...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.16,0:08:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I get all wishy washy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.38,0:08:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you've gotta go some place where you'll NEVER melt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.72,0:08:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The only place I'd never melt is the north pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.06,0:08:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we've got to get you there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.44,0:08:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we'll take you downtown to the railroad station and put you on a train.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.34,0:08:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Great, I always wanted to see the town. Let's make a party out of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.56,0:08:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have a parade!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.20,0:09:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[Frosty the snowman knew the sun was hot that day, so he said let's run and we'll have some fun now before I melt away.]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.98,0:09:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[Down to the village with a broomstick in his hand, running here and there all around the square, saying catch me if you can.]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.80,0:09:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on kids, follow the leader!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.06,0:10:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,[He led them down the streets of town right to the traffic cop, and he only paused a moment when he heard him holler stop.]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.48,0:10:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[Cop blows whistle] Stop.  STOP.  STOP!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.90,0:11:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, didn't you see that traffic light?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.00,0:10:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's a traffic light?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.64,0:10:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Up there on the lamp post!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.76,0:10:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What's a lamp post?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.36,0:10:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, do you want a ticket, wise guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.62,0:10:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love one, to the north pole, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.04,0:10:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to excuse him, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.16,0:10:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, he just came  to life and he doesn't know much about such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.92,0:10:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, okay, if he just came to life. [Cop blows whistle] Move along!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.42,0:10:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Them silly snowmen.  Once they come to life they don't know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.32,0:10:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to life?!  [Soft whistling]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.92,0:11:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[Snoring]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.68,0:11:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like a ticket to the north pole please.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.44,0:11:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... What?  Yes.  The north pole?  Oh, yes ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.04,0:11:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[BONK, PING, TINKLE, SCRABBLE, DOINK]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.18,0:11:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Route you by the way of Saskatchewan, Hudson Bay, Nome Alaska, the Klondike, and Aurora Borealis!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.72,0:11:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta make a change at Nanuk of the Northville.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.34,0:11:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll be $3,000 and four cents, including tax.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.78,0:11:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but we don't have any money...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.74,0:11:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No money!? [BONK, PING, TINKLE, SCRABBLE, DOINK]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.42,0:12:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No money, no ticket! [SLAM!]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.92,0:12:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[Sad music plays]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.28,0:12:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'll never get to the north pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.80,0:12:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Frosty, you just can't melt!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Karen, don't you get all slushy too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.30,0:12:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Hocus?  Out the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.68,0:12:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A refrigerated boxcar on a train headed north. You'll be safe there, Frosty!  Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.08,0:12:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's full of ice cream and frozen Christmas cakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.26,0:12:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What a neat way to travel!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.50,0:12:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[Whistle blows]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.50,0:12:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, Frosty, the train is pulling out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.14,0:13:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you coming to the north pole, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.50,0:13:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure my mother won't mind, as long as I'm home in time for supper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.26,0:13:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[Whistle blows]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.74,0:13:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[Frosty the snowman had to hurry on his way, but he waved goodbye saying don't cry. I'll be back again some day.]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.26,0:13:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I must get that hat back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.72,0:13:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Think, nasty, think, nasty, think nasty.  [Evil laughter].
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.14,0:13:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[He'll be back again some daaaaaaaaaay.]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.02,0:13:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now actually, a refrigerated boxcar is a splendid way to travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.58,0:14:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid that is... if one is a snowman or a furry coated rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But for Karen...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.34,0:14:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,[Sneeze] Are you cold, Karen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.08,0:14:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's a silly question.  You wouldn't be sneezing if you weren't cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... just... just a lit... little. [Sneeze]
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.50,0:14:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Frosty realized that Karen had to get out of that car as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.82,0:14:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the little freight train stopped to let an express full of happy Christmas travelers pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.02,0:14:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Frosty took advantage of the opportunity and quickly got them all off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.00,0:14:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you tricked me!  NO FAIR!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.68,0:14:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing professor Hinkle could do was make a jump for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.62,0:15:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,[BONK, PING, TINKLE, SHATTER, DOINK]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.26,0:15:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[Howling wind]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.86,0:15:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Frosty wanted to get as far away as he could before Hinkle woke up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.24,0:15:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,[Hocus' teeth chatter]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.90,0:15:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[Sneeze]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.88,0:15:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But the woods through which they traveled were still bitterly cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.74,0:15:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hocus, I've got to get Karen all warmed up or she's a gonner!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.78,0:15:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't make a fire.  Oh boy, that's one thing I really can't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we just better keep moving until we find somebody who can.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.76,0:16:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then suddenly they came upon a tiny glen which seemed almost magical.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.44,0:16:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,For it was Christmas eve and the woodland animals were all decorating for their big celebration.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.78,0:16:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They knew Santa was to come that night and they wanted everything to be just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.24,0:16:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hocus, speak to the animals.  See if they won't all pitch in and build a fire for Karen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.32,0:16:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[Squeaky noises]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.28,0:16:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The animals were delighted to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.42,0:16:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so they found a spot away from the glen where the fire wouldn't catch on to the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.44,0:16:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon there was a spark and in almost no time a splendid fire was crackling away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.12,0:17:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Frosty was careful to stay far away from the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.50,0:17:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hocus, we've got to find someone to help Karen get home before she freezes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.16,0:17:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And me to the north pole before I melt, but who?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.38,0:17:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not the Marines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.32,0:17:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not the president of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.95,0:17:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, they were both swell ideas, but we've got to find someone nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.62,0:17:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Santa Claus.  That's a great idea. Why didn't I think of that before?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.38,0:17:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hocus, you go back with the animals and when Santa comes, you bring him right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.72,0:17:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.81,0:17:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.23,0:18:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So Frosty kept a silent vigil,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.45,0:18:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,waiting patiently all through the night until Santa would arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.25,0:18:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.04,0:18:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, a campfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.79,0:18:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well isn't that all snug and comfy? [Evil laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.31,0:18:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[Professor Hinkle blows]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.18,0:18:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No!  Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.16,0:18:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now give me that hat or else!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.46,0:18:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Or else what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.36,0:18:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well don't bother me with details, give me that hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.10,0:18:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Get on my shoulders, Karen!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.95,0:18:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Frosty, since he was made of snow  himself was the fastest belly-whopper in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.31,0:18:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And old professor Hinkle was soon far outdistanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.02,0:19:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it was Frosty's good fortune that right at the bottom of the hill was a tiny greenhouse
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.92,0:19:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,used to grow precious tropical poinsettias for Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.12,0:19:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got to be all warm and snug inside for those Christmas flowers to grow so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.32,0:19:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.03,0:19:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but, but you will melt!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.92,0:19:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little.  I'll only stay inside for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.60,0:19:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I've been meaning to take off a little weight anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.15,0:19:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew, stay in here much longer and I'll REALLY make a splash in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.37,0:20:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I've got you, and the minute you're all melted the hat will be mine! [Evil laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.68,0:20:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Santa had arrived but was he too late?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.16,0:20:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hocus explained the situation to Santa, who (as you know) speaks a fluent rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.58,0:20:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they didn't find Frosty and Karen on the hill...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.81,0:20:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Santa followed Frosty's path in the snow to the greenhouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.30,0:20:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But when they got inside, a terrible sight met their eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.23,0:20:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,[Karen weeping] [Sad music plays]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.66,0:21:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,[(Very slowly) Frosty the snowman was a happy, jolly soul with a corn-cob pipe and a button nose and two eyes made out of coal.]
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.78,0:21:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They were too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.68,0:21:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Too late?  Why, nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.00,0:21:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't cry, Karen. Frosty's not gone for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.30,0:21:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, he was made out of Christmas snow
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.61,0:21:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and Christmas snow can never disappear completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.36,0:21:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it sometimes goes away for almost a year at a time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.47,0:21:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and takes the form of Spring and Summer rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.57,0:22:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can bet your boots that when a good jolly December wind kisses it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.16,0:22:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it will turn in to Christmas snow all over again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.64,0:22:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but he was my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.22,0:22:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[Chuckle] Just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.18,0:22:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,WAIT A MINUTE!  I want that hat and I want it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.91,0:22:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you dare touch that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.76,0:22:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And just what are YOU going to do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.33,0:22:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you so much as lay a finger on the brim,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.51,0:22:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never bring you another Christmas present as long as you live.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.25,0:22:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Never?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.38,0:22:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.42,0:22:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No more trick cards or magic balls or...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.68,0:22:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No more anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.03,0:23:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.52,0:23:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we evil magicians have to make a living too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.32,0:23:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you go home and write "I am very sorry for what I did to Frosty" a hundred zillion times.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.11,0:23:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And then maybe, just maybe, mind you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.79,0:23:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find something in your stocking tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.39,0:23:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A new hat maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.42,0:23:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,, Oh, yes sir.  Goodbye everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.78,0:23:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to lose and run, but I've got to get busy writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.16,0:23:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Busy busy busy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.54,0:23:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Frosty, we're all waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.23,0:23:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,HAPPY BIRTHDAY!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.35,0:23:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[Frosty the snowman is a fairy-tale they say. He was made of snow but the children know how he came to life one day.]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.76,0:24:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And so Santa took Karen home and made ready to bring Frosty back to the north pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.18,0:24:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Karen hated to say goodbye to Frosty,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.67,0:24:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but as Santa promised, Frosty returned every year with the magical Christmas snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.80,0:24:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,  And every year there was a great celebration with a great Christmas parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.03,0:24:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[Thumpity thump thump thumpity thump. Look at that Frosty go. Thumpity thump thump thumpity thump. Over the hills of snow.]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.17,0:24:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[Frosty the snowman, was a jolly, happy soul. With a corn-cob pipe and a button nose, and two eyes made out of coal.]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.36,0:24:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And with Frosty the snowman, Christmas was always very merry indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.71,0:25:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a merry Christmas too!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.63,0:25:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[Frosty the snowman had to hurry on his way, but he waved goodbye saying don't you cry...]
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.47,0:25:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be back on Christmas day!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.98,0:25:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas - To: Robyn. From: Dan.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.98,0:25:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And Merry Christmas to the pirates of the intarnets!

